      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint and acceptance criterion RH < 1.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is computed as the ratio of device NIH to predicate NIH. This QoI directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion and is clinically meaningful for CPB hemolysis risk assessment."
